# Testing Infrastructure - README

## Overview

This project uses **Vitest** as the testing framework, providing fast unit and integration testing capabilities.

## Test Structure

```
__tests__/
├── unit/                  # Unit tests for use cases
│   └── use-cases/        # Use case tests
├── integration/          # Integration tests
│   └── repositories/     # Repository tests
├── e2e/                  # End-to-end tests
├── mocks/                # Mock implementations
├── fixtures/             # Test data fixtures
└── setup.ts              # Global test setup
```

## Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Run tests with UI
npm run test:ui

# Run tests with coverage
npm run test:coverage

# Run only unit tests
npm run test:unit

# Run only integration tests
npm run test:integration

# Run only E2E tests
npm run test:e2e

# Watch mode (default)
npm test
```

## Writing Tests

### Unit Tests for Use Cases

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';
import { YourUseCase } from '@/modules/your-module';
import { MockRepository } from '@/__tests__/mocks/MockRepository';

describe('YourUseCase', () => {
  let useCase: YourUseCase;
  let mockRepo: MockRepository;

  beforeEach(() => {
    mockRepo = new MockRepository();
    useCase = new YourUseCase(mockRepo);
  });

  it('should do something', async () => {
    // Arrange
    const input = { /* test data */ };

    // Act
    const result = await useCase.execute(input);

    // Assert
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

### Integration Tests for Repositories

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { SupabaseYourRepository } from '@/modules/your-module';

describe('SupabaseYourRepository', () => {
  it('should create entity', async () => {
    // Test with actual database calls
  });
});
```

## Test Coverage

Run coverage reports with:
```bash
npm run test:coverage
```

Coverage reports are generated in `coverage/` directory.

